value.value: 腎アルブミン再吸収異常
any anomaly in the process in which albumin is taken up from the collecting ducts and proximal and distal loops of the nephron
腎グルコース再吸収異常
any anomaly in the process in which glucose is taken up from the collecting ducts and proximal and distal loops of the nephron
ドーパミン作動性ニューロン数の減少
fewer than normal numbers of the neurons that utilize dopamine as a neurotransmitter
ドーパミン作動性ニューロン数の増加
greater than normal numbers of the neurons that utilize dopamine as a neurotransmitter
異所性ドーパミン作動性ニューロン
abnormal location of one or more of the neurons that utilize dopamine as a neurotransmitter

糸球体毛細血管内皮の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the thin, extremely flattened layer of cells that line the interior surface of glomerular capillaries and is densely perforated by large transcellular pores (aka fenestrae or fenestrations) that, unlike those of other fenestrated capillaries, are generally thought to lack diaphragms
糸球体内皮窓の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the large plasma membrane-lined circular pores that perforate the flattened glomerular endothelium and, unlike those of other fenestrated capillaries, are not spanned by diaphragms; the density and size of glomerular fenestrae account, at least in part, for the high permeability of the glomerular capillary wall to water and small solutes
糸球体内皮窓の欠如

absence of the large plasma membrane-lined circular pores that normally perforate the flattened glomerular endothelium; loss of fenestrae may lead to a reduction in the glomerular filtration rate or proteinuria
尿管芽の発生異常
any anomaly in the development of the elongated stalk of the ureteric bud that contributes to the morphogenesis of the ureter; the ureter ureteric bud is the initial structure that forms the ureter
後腎尿管芽の発生異常
any anomaly in the development of the portion of the ureteric bud tube that contributes to the morphogenesis of the metanephros
尿中塩素イオン濃度異常
any change in the amount of chloride ion in the urine
尿中塩素イオン濃度上昇
abnormally large amounts of chloride ion in the urine
尿中塩素イオン濃度低下
abnormally low amounts of chloride ion in the urine
尿中炭酸水素塩の濃度異常
any change in the amount of bicarbonate in the urine
尿中炭酸水素塩濃度上昇
an increased amount of bicarbonate in the urine compared to the normal state
尿中炭酸水素塩濃度低下
a reduced amount of bicarbonate in the urine compared to the normal state
ビリルビン尿
presence of conjugated bilirubin in the urine
尿中尿素窒素の値異常
any change in the amount of nitrogen in the form of urea in the urine
尿中尿素窒素濃度上昇
abnormally high amounts of nitrogen in the form of urea in the urine
尿中尿素窒素濃度低下
abnormally low amounts of nitrogen in the form of urea in the urine
尿中アミノ酸濃度異常
any anomaly in the amount in the urine of a carboxylic acid containing one or more amino groups (-NH2) and a carboxyl (-COOH) group
尿中クレアチニン濃度異常
any change in the amount of creatinine in the urine
尿中クレアチニン濃度上昇
an increased amount of creatinine in the urine compared to the normal state
尿中クレアチニン濃度低下
a reduced amount of creatinine in the urine compared to the normal state
尿中グリコサミングリカン濃度異常

any change in the amount of glycosaminoglycan in the urine, including chondroitin sulfate, dermatan sulfate, keratan sulfate, heparin sulfate, heparin, and/or hyaluronan and other long unbranched polysaccharides consisting of a repeating disaccharide unit
尿中グリコサミングリカン濃度上昇

greater in the amount of glycosaminoglycan in the urine, including chondroitin sulfate, dermatan sulfate, keratan sulfate, heparin sulfate, heparin, and/or hyaluronan and other long unbranched polysaccharides consisting of a repeating disaccharide unit
尿中グリコサミングリカン濃度低下

reduced amount of glycosaminoglycan in the urine, including chondroitin sulfate, dermatan sulfate, keratan sulfate, heparin sulfate, heparin, and/or hyaluronan and other long unbranched polysaccharides consisting of a repeating disaccharide unit
グリコサミノグリカン値異常

any change in the amount of glycosaminoglycan, including chondroitin sulfate, dermatan sulfate, keratan sulfate, heparin sulfate, heparin, and/or hyaluronan and other long unbranched polysaccharides consisting of a repeating disaccharide unit
尿ヌクレオチドの値異常

any change in the urinary level of glycosamines consisting of a nucleobase, a five-carbon sugar moiety (ribose or deoxyribose), and may be mono-, di- or triphosphate; this definition includes cyclic-nucleotides (nucleoside cyclic phosphates)
尿ヌクレオシドの値異常

any change in the urinary level of glycosylamines consisting of a nucleobase bound to a ribose or deoxyribose sugar via a beta-glycosidic linkage, including cytidine, uridine, adenosine, guanosine, thymidine and inosine and deoxynucleosides
尿中カテコラミン濃度異常

any anomaly in the urinary amount of catecholamines, including adrenaline, noradrenaline and L-dopamine; catecholamines act as hormones or neurotransmitters and are derived from the amino acid tyrosine
カテコラミンの値異常
any anomaly in the amount of catecholamines, including adrenaline, noradrenaline and L-dopamine; catecholamines are act as hormones or neurotransmitters and are derived from the amino acid tyrosine
尿管蠕動障害
any anomaly in the wavelike sequence of involuntary muscular contraction and relaxation that passes along the ureter, thus propelling urine from the kidney pelvis to the urinary bladder
虹彩前癒着
adhesion of the iris to the cornea
虹彩後癒着
adhesion of the iris to the capsule of the lens or to the surface of the vitreous body
腎糸球体癒着

presence of adhesions (synechiae) between the Bowman's capsule and the glomerular tuft; may develop when areas of glomerular capillary basement membrane denuded of visceral epithelial cells come in contact with the parietal epithelium of Bowman's capsule
尿管尿路上皮の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the epithelial lining of the luminal space of the ureter
尿道尿路上皮の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the epithelial lining of the luminal space of the urethra
異所性子宮

an abnormally placed opening of the ureter, either into the urinary bladder or at another site in the lower urinary or genital tract; commonly a result of a duplicated renal collecting system, a duplex kidney with two ureters where usually one ureter terminates at the urinary bladder, while the duplicated ureter being ectopic, ends in the vagina, the urethra or the vulval vestibule
腎盂尿管移行部の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the junction between the ureter and the renal pelvis of the kidney
尿管膀胱移行部の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the valve-like structure found at the site of entry of the ureter into the urinary bladder, normally displays an oblique angulation through the detrusor to avoid reflux of urine up the ureters and the kidney
腎盂尿管移行部の閉鎖
congenital absence or closure of the connection between the ureter and the renal pelvis
腎盂尿管移行部の狭窄
abnormal narrowing or constriction of the junction between the ureter and the renal pelvis
腎盂尿管移行部の閉塞
a partial or total blockage of the flow of urine through the junction of the renal pelvis and the proximal ureter
尿管膀胱移行部の閉塞
a partial or total blockage of the valve-like structure found at the site of entry of the ureter into the urinary bladder
重複尿管

two ureters open separately into the renal pelvis superiorly and drain separately into the urinary bladder or genital tract; if two ureteral buds arise from the Wolffian duct, a duplex kidney with complete ureteral duplication ensues where the additional ureter may result in a ureterocele, or an ectopic ureter
色素沈着パターンの異常
hair and/or skin coloration shows specific and consistent deviations from an expected display
頭部の形状異常
any anomaly in the characteristic surface outline or contour of a head of an organism
